Diageo May Buy Polish Vodka Maker Stock Spirits, Times Reports

-- B y   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 
2011-03-13T12:03:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/diageo-may-buy-polish-vodka-maker-stock-spirits-times-reports.html
  Diageo Plc (DGE)  may spend 500 million
pounds ($804 million) to buy Stock Spirits, the producer of the
Polish vodka Czysta de Luxe, the  Sunday Times  reported.  The bid for the U.K.-based company is part of a plan to
expand into emerging markets, driven by Diageo Chief Executive
Officer Paul Walsh, the Times reported, without saying where it
got its information.  Stephen Doherty, a spokesman for the London-based company,
declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kari Lundgren in London at 
 klundgren2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Will Kennedy  at 
 wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  